ws to bypass\nthe computational burden of a large-volume real high-resolution simulation\nwithout much compromise in the mass resolution of the result. The cost of our\nML approach ($\\sim 1$ CPU-hour) is negligible compared to the cost of a\n$N$-body simulation (e.g. millions of CPU-hours), The required computing time\nis cut a factor of 8.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 23 Mar 2022 18:51:58 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 25 Apr 2022 19:30:23 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 29 Apr 2022 14:52:47 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-01"}
