amma$-exchange correction in muonic deuterium appears to be completely\neliminated. To further confirm this, we revisit the hydrogen-deuterium isotope\nshift in the same framework. Our work provides an alternative self-consistent\nand high-precision evaluation of the $2\\gamma$-exchange correction in (muonic)\ndeuterium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 24 Mar 2022 12:17:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-07-05"}
